Interface IBinarySearchTree<TKey extends Comparable<TKey>,Value>

Type Parameters:
TKey - the type of keys maintained by this tree, must be comparable
Value - the type of mapped values
All Known Implementing Classes:
BinarySearchTree
public interface IBinarySearchTree<TKey extends Comparable<TKey>,Value>
Interface for a Binary Search Tree (BST). Defines the standard operations that a BST should support.

    • insert

      void insert(TKey key, Value value)
      Inserts a new key-value pair into the tree. If the key already exists, its corresponding value may be updated.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to insert
      value - the value associated with the key

    • delete

      void delete(TKey key)
      Deletes the mapping for a key from this tree if it is present.
      Parameters:

    • contains

      boolean contains(TKey key)
      Searches for a key in the tree.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to search for
      Returns:
      true if the tree contains a mapping for the specified key, false otherwise

    • get

      Value get(TKey key)
      Retrieves the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this tree contains no mapping for the key.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose associated value is to be returned
      Returns:
      the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this tree contains no mapping for the key

    • update

      void update(TKey key, Value value)
      Updates the value associated with a specified key. If the key does not exist, this operation may or may not insert it, depending on the implementation.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose associated value is to be updated
      value - the new value to associate with the key

    • height

      int height()
      Returns the height of the tree. The height of an empty tree is typically defined as -1, and a tree with one node as 0.
      Returns:
      the height of the tree
